WEBVTT

00:01.871 --> 00:02.959
ADULT ADAM:
For as long
as I can remember,

00:03.046 --> 00:05.005
Beverly Goldberg
loved to dance.

00:05.092 --> 00:07.485
Sure, her fearless mom moves
were embarrassing,

00:07.572 --> 00:10.010
but you had to admire
her pure passion.

00:10.097 --> 00:11.446
You can't blame the lady.

00:11.533 --> 00:12.969
This was the '80s,

00:13.056 --> 00:15.189
the golden age
of the cheesy dance movie,

00:15.276 --> 00:16.712
most notably,
Flashdance,

00:16.799 --> 00:18.279
the tale
of a working-class girl

00:18.366 --> 00:21.238
who wanted to boogie
with the best.

00:21.325 --> 00:23.284
I don't think
she's ever gonna get
into this dance school.

00:23.371 --> 00:25.199
Even the lady judge
isn't supporting her.

00:25.286 --> 00:26.722
This movie is insane.

00:26.809 --> 00:28.680
She's so graceful
and yet from Pittsburgh?

00:28.767 --> 00:30.204
Shh!
Screw you!

00:30.291 --> 00:32.075
Some people!
Jerk!

00:32.162 --> 00:34.077
ADULT ADAM: But,
as fate would have it,
that year,

00:34.164 --> 00:36.514
flashdancing made its way
to Jenkintown.

00:36.601 --> 00:38.734
Break out your hottest
leg warmers, ladies!

00:38.821 --> 00:40.475
It's time to flashdance.

00:40.562 --> 00:43.869
"Bring your boogie-woogie
and a towel"? Ehh.

00:43.956 --> 00:47.047
Come on.
It's our chance to live
the very realistic story

00:47.134 --> 00:49.179
of a steelworker
turned modern dancer.

00:49.266 --> 00:52.008
Please! No one wants to
see four moms

00:52.095 --> 00:54.532
shake their tushes
at the JCC.

00:54.619 --> 00:56.447
Our entire lives revolve
around our kids.

00:56.534 --> 00:58.406
But I have learned
something very important

00:58.493 --> 00:59.537
from the Bevolution.

00:59.624 --> 01:02.062
Is that still a thing?
The biggest.

01:02.149 --> 01:05.587
And it's taught me that unless
we make time for ourselves,

01:05.674 --> 01:07.676
our wonderful families
will leech us dry

01:07.763 --> 01:09.417
of our youth and spirit.

01:09.504 --> 01:11.767
I guess I do have
a little time
between school drop off

01:11.854 --> 01:13.899
and school pick up, and sports
drop off and sports pick up.

01:13.986 --> 01:15.901
Well, it sounds like a small
window, but I'll take it.

01:15.988 --> 01:17.729
How about you gals?
Maybe it wouldn't hurt

01:17.816 --> 01:20.471
to stay in the back
of the class
and pick up a few moves.

01:20.558 --> 01:22.734
ADULT ADAM:
While they didn't stay
in the back of the class,

01:22.821 --> 01:24.780
they did pick up
a few moves...

01:24.867 --> 01:28.044
Or whatever this is.

01:30.742 --> 01:32.004
INSTRUCTOR: And pose!

01:32.092 --> 01:34.094
Not bad, ladies.

01:34.181 --> 01:37.271
Not bad? Uh, we have
taken our passion
and made it happen!

01:37.358 --> 01:39.882
Whoo-hoo!

01:39.969 --> 01:41.579
♪♪

01:41.666 --> 01:43.059
ANDY: Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on, fellas.

01:43.146 --> 01:45.148
Dance class just let out.

01:45.235 --> 01:47.672
Now, this is why we come
to the Jenkintown JCC.

01:47.759 --> 01:49.283
Aw, yeah.

01:49.370 --> 01:51.328
Wait, I take it back!
That's my mom!

01:51.415 --> 01:52.764
And she's with my mom!

01:52.851 --> 01:55.289
Hey, Bar. Don't hug Mama,
she's aglow with dance.

01:55.376 --> 01:56.899
Why is your shoulder
exposed?

01:56.986 --> 01:58.422
Mama's just flashdancing.

01:58.509 --> 01:59.815
Well, you're flashing
too much!

01:59.902 --> 02:01.643
Don't listen to him,
hot moms.

02:01.730 --> 02:04.602
Johnny Atkins
is a shoulder man.

02:04.689 --> 02:06.213
They all look encouraged
by his creepy words.

02:06.300 --> 02:07.997
Barry, do something!
What?

02:08.084 --> 02:09.651
Cover your shoulder with
my sweat towel! Right now!

02:09.738 --> 02:11.305
Please.

02:11.392 --> 02:12.610
Okay, stop it.
Just stop.Get off of me.

02:12.697 --> 02:14.351
Get out of here.
Just get out of here.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.136
♪ I'm twisted up inside

02:16.223 --> 02:18.747
♪ But nonetheless
I feel the need to say

02:22.142 --> 02:23.752
♪ I don't know the future

02:23.839 --> 02:27.364
♪ But the past keeps getting
clearer every day ♪

02:27.451 --> 02:29.018
ADULT ADAM:
It was April 11,
1980-something,

02:29.105 --> 02:30.672
a typical Saturday night

02:30.759 --> 02:32.848
for me and my best friend,
Emmy Mirsky.

02:32.935 --> 02:35.242
God, I love Blades of Steel.I call Penguins!

02:35.329 --> 02:37.069
Why do you always
choose the stupid Penguins?

02:37.157 --> 02:39.071
'Cause they're my favorite
animal. Also, they do this.

02:39.159 --> 02:41.596
ADAM:
And I'm down.

02:41.683 --> 02:43.250
You just make it easy
by sucking.

02:43.337 --> 02:45.948
ADULT ADAM: It was more than a friendship. Emmy was like my sister.

02:46.035 --> 02:48.255
Ever since we were kids,
we did everything together,

02:48.342 --> 02:51.345
from Nintendo marathons to treehouse slumber parties.

02:51.432 --> 02:53.477
Brian McMahon made it
pretty darn clear.

02:53.564 --> 02:55.784
Do you like him,
yes or no?

02:55.871 --> 02:57.873
You know what?
I'm marking yes.

02:57.960 --> 03:00.789
And best of all,
our traditions continued
through high school.

03:00.876 --> 03:02.965
I don't know, Muscles.
Your mom is super against

03:03.052 --> 03:04.358
getting your ears pierced.
Just do it, nerd!

03:04.445 --> 03:05.837
Okay.

03:05.924 --> 03:08.579
Three, two, one, and...

03:10.581 --> 03:13.454
All right,
welcome to pickleball!

03:13.541 --> 03:16.239
Do not be fooled by its
comically delightful name.

03:16.326 --> 03:18.285
Pickleball
is a serious sport.

03:18.372 --> 03:19.808
It combines
the greatest elements

03:19.895 --> 03:22.027
of tennis, badminton,
and Ping-Pong.

03:22.114 --> 03:23.638
Time to pick
your pickleball partner.

03:23.725 --> 03:25.292
Just make sure your partner
for pickleball

03:25.379 --> 03:26.815
doesn't already have
a pickleball partner picked!

03:26.902 --> 03:28.730
Let's go! Let's go!
Let's go!

03:28.817 --> 03:31.298
You wanna play forehand
or backhand?
I'm super bad at both.

03:31.385 --> 03:33.125
Uh, actually,
Brian McMahon

03:33.213 --> 03:35.389
already asked me
to play with him.

03:35.476 --> 03:37.739
ADULT ADAM: This was Brian,
one of the most
popular kids in school.

03:37.826 --> 03:40.350
The dude was painfully shy,
but he made it look cool.

03:40.437 --> 03:42.526
Wow, Shy Bri
actually talked to you?

03:42.613 --> 03:43.919
See ya at lunch!

03:44.006 --> 03:45.834
No partner,
huh, Goldfarb?

03:45.921 --> 03:47.749
Eh, it's all right.
No shame in that.

03:47.836 --> 03:49.925
At least that's what
the school instructs me
to say.

03:50.012 --> 03:53.668
Maybe I can just do
a related assignment
like eat a pickle?

03:53.755 --> 03:56.148
Don't worry, Coach
has got your back.

03:56.236 --> 03:57.889
Now engage your core!
Let's go!

03:57.976 --> 03:59.195
♪♪

03:59.282 --> 04:00.414
Yah!

04:00.501 --> 04:01.632
Mine! Mine! Mine! Ah!

04:01.719 --> 04:03.460
There's the beef!
All me! All me!

04:03.547 --> 04:05.157
I got it!
I got it! I got it!

04:05.245 --> 04:06.898
Eat my shorts!

04:06.985 --> 04:08.857
Get out of the way!

04:08.944 --> 04:10.250
Yah!

04:10.337 --> 04:12.077
That's game! 21-zip!

04:12.164 --> 04:13.601
Learn from it.

04:13.688 --> 04:15.559
I learned
that this game sucks.

04:15.646 --> 04:17.822
Ha! He's mocking
what you care about.

04:17.909 --> 04:19.389
Laps! Now!

04:19.476 --> 04:21.957
Both of you,
let's go!

04:22.044 --> 04:24.699
And as for you, if we're gonna
pair up again tomorrow.

04:24.786 --> 04:26.309
I need you to run some drills
after school.

04:26.396 --> 04:27.702
Bring six gallons
of water.

04:27.789 --> 04:30.139
Thanks, but I'll be back
with Emmy next class.

04:30.226 --> 04:33.098
Yo, we're grabbing
some Gino's for lunch.Rad! I love Gino's!

04:33.185 --> 04:35.840
If I'm not back
for study hall, cover for me.

04:35.927 --> 04:39.148
Oof! That was
tough to watch.

04:39.235 --> 04:40.845
Well, Coach
is here for you.

04:40.932 --> 04:42.151
Except during lunch.

04:42.238 --> 04:44.371
That's when I have
my 67-vegetable smoothie.

04:44.458 --> 04:46.198
But I'm happy to talk
again on my jog home.

04:46.286 --> 04:48.636
Emmy's been my best friend
since second grade.

04:48.723 --> 04:50.246
Dating Brian
won't change anything.

04:50.333 --> 04:51.682
All right, listen up.

04:51.769 --> 04:53.597
Part of growing up
is growing apart.

04:53.684 --> 04:54.990
You and Emmy are always
gonna be friends,

04:55.077 --> 04:56.905
even if you don't hang out
or talk

04:56.992 --> 04:59.647
or she can't recall
your name immediately.

04:59.734 --> 05:02.127
How am I doing?
You feeling any better?

05:02.214 --> 05:05.305
Not at all!
Yeah, this one
got away from me.

05:05.392 --> 05:07.916
ADULT ADAM: As I panicked about my future with my best friend,

05:08.003 --> 05:10.440
Barry couldn't get past
our mom's new hobby.

05:10.527 --> 05:14.096
The JCC All Ages
Dance Recital?

05:14.183 --> 05:16.403
It is a celebration
of the sweet moves

05:16.490 --> 05:18.622
we learned from 4:00
to 6:00 on Tuesdays.
And you're going.

05:18.709 --> 05:20.450
Adam, come in here
and get my back!

05:20.537 --> 05:22.017
This is gonna
traumatize you, too.

05:22.104 --> 05:23.584
Unlikely.
There's nothing worse

05:23.671 --> 05:25.020
than losing your oldest
and dearest friend

05:25.107 --> 05:26.195
to the popular crowd.

05:26.282 --> 05:27.892
Uck, I literally
just fell asleep.

05:27.979 --> 05:30.330
Dad! Kill
her dance dreams now!

05:30.417 --> 05:32.462
Just go to her damn show
and let me know how it went.

05:32.549 --> 05:34.246
Oh, no,
you're going, too.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.727
Can't. I got a work thing.
You don't even know
when it is!

05:36.814 --> 05:38.163
And I have
a work thing, too.

05:38.250 --> 05:39.904
You don't even have a job!
That checks out.

05:39.991 --> 05:41.558
You are gonna support
your loving mother

05:41.645 --> 05:43.604
because she has supported
everything

05:43.691 --> 05:45.954
her precious babies
have ever done.

05:46.041 --> 05:48.652
Dammit! I am so jealous
Erica escaped this house

05:48.739 --> 05:50.262
and made it to college.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.656
ERICA:
Where are they?
My life is over!

05:52.743 --> 05:54.136
Where are the pictures
of my boyfriend

05:54.223 --> 05:55.790
making out with that skank
Bridget Greenley?

05:55.877 --> 05:57.922
Surprise!

05:58.009 --> 05:59.663
Geoff's not cheating on you.

05:59.750 --> 06:01.752
I just lied to get you here.
Isn't that fun?

06:01.839 --> 06:04.189
I drove home from D.C.
at 90 miles an hour

06:04.276 --> 06:05.626
with tears in my eyes!

06:05.713 --> 06:07.889
Well, the good news is,
your love is still intact

06:07.976 --> 06:10.892
and your mother has
a dance recital tomorrow!

06:10.979 --> 06:13.895
Ha! You have to
sit through Mom's
gyrating garbage with us.

06:13.982 --> 06:15.940
All right, I can tell
from the hateful language

06:16.027 --> 06:17.594
that I have doubters here,

06:17.681 --> 06:19.422
which is why I'm going to
give you

06:19.509 --> 06:20.945
a little preview
of what's in store.

06:22.469 --> 06:24.514
♪ First
when there's nothing♪

06:24.601 --> 06:26.908
ADULT ADAM: And with that,
my mom took her six weeks

06:26.995 --> 06:29.084
of rigorous JCC training

06:29.171 --> 06:31.521
and put her heart
and soul on the line.

06:31.608 --> 06:34.219
♪ That your fear
seems to hide♪

06:34.306 --> 06:36.308
Much like the toe-tapping
Jennifer Beals' audition

06:36.396 --> 06:38.310
inFlashdance,

06:38.398 --> 06:40.487
Beverly Goldberg
would win over
her condescending critics

06:40.574 --> 06:42.706
using the soaring magic
of dance.

06:42.793 --> 06:47.058
♪ All alone, I have cried♪

06:47.145 --> 06:52.716
♪ Silent tears
full of pride♪

06:52.803 --> 06:57.417
♪ In a world made of steel♪

06:57.504 --> 06:59.854
♪ Made of stone♪

07:01.812 --> 07:05.512
♪♪

07:05.599 --> 07:08.819
♪ What a feeling♪

07:08.906 --> 07:12.649
♪ Being's believin'♪

07:12.736 --> 07:15.086
♪ I can have it all♪

07:15.173 --> 07:19.830
♪ Now I'm dancing
for my life♪

07:19.917 --> 07:21.571
You've been flashdanced!

07:29.405 --> 07:31.625
Thank you
for bringing me home
from college to see this!

07:31.712 --> 07:33.061
I can't breathe!

07:33.148 --> 07:38.109
It hurts!
It's so funny it hurts!

07:38.196 --> 07:39.676
Seriously?

07:39.763 --> 07:42.897
You're laughing at me after
I just danced my heart out?

07:42.984 --> 07:45.073
Thanks, Mom!
I needed a good laugh.

07:45.160 --> 07:48.293
It hurts! Aah! Oh.

07:51.471 --> 07:52.515
Are you okay, Dad?

07:52.602 --> 07:54.082
No, he's not okay!

07:54.169 --> 07:55.866
He literally
injured himself
laughing at me!

07:58.086 --> 07:59.870
Enough!

07:59.957 --> 08:02.046
All you people do
is call me a smother
and beg me to change.

08:02.133 --> 08:03.526
And then
when I finally try to do it,

08:03.613 --> 08:04.875
you mock me
with your mean spirits!

08:04.962 --> 08:06.573
Thank you.
This is the most fun

08:06.660 --> 08:08.705
that we've had as a family
in a long time.

08:08.792 --> 08:10.881
Ha! So funny!

08:10.968 --> 08:12.709
Ohh!
I popped something else!

08:12.796 --> 08:15.843
Gotta go back.
Aaah! Aah!

08:15.930 --> 08:17.105
Great-grandpa's balls!

08:18.323 --> 08:20.238
Jackie, huge news!

08:20.325 --> 08:21.936
We're gonna double date
with Emmy and her new beau!

08:22.023 --> 08:23.328
Oh, my God,
Emmy has a boyfriend?

08:23.415 --> 08:25.026
Not yet. But she will

08:25.113 --> 08:26.375
once I play
a little yenta matchmaker.

08:26.462 --> 08:27.550
Aw, you're gonna
set her up?

08:27.637 --> 08:29.073
Yep, I'm the best.

08:29.160 --> 08:31.032
Now time to find Emmy
a sweet, kind dude

08:31.119 --> 08:33.208
who isn't popular
or threatening
to me in any way.

08:35.123 --> 08:36.472
Muscles Mirsky!

08:36.559 --> 08:39.040
What if I told you there's
three eligible bachelors

08:39.127 --> 08:40.868
just waiting to become
your boyfriend?

08:40.955 --> 08:44.088
Mr. Goldberg,
this is study hall,
not The Dating Game.

08:44.175 --> 08:45.873
This'll only take a minute.

08:45.960 --> 08:47.657
Let's meet
bachelor number one!

08:47.744 --> 08:50.660
He's exotic.
He's mysterious.
He's Sergei!

08:50.747 --> 08:52.749
Good hello, sturdy woman.

08:52.836 --> 08:54.969
This joker?
You can't be serious.

08:55.056 --> 08:57.406
Sergei still happy
he got out there.

08:57.493 --> 08:58.973
Okay, rough start.

08:59.060 --> 09:00.888
Bachelor number two
is a tall glass of water

09:00.975 --> 09:02.585
who plays clarinet
in marching band...

09:02.672 --> 09:04.761
It's me, Dan!
I couldn't wait for him
to finish speaking!

09:04.848 --> 09:07.808
Keep walkin', Dan-O.
Thank you for
the opportunity to compete.

09:07.895 --> 09:09.461
Saving the best for last!
Bachelor number three!

09:09.549 --> 09:10.550
It better not be
Dave Kim.

09:10.637 --> 09:13.291
What? I would never!

09:13.378 --> 09:16.512
Look, I appreciate
the crappy effort.

09:16.599 --> 09:19.123
But... I kinda spent lunch
making out
with Brian McMahon.

09:19.210 --> 09:20.951
What do you even see
in that guy?

09:21.038 --> 09:23.911
He's handsome
and athletic and cool.

09:23.998 --> 09:25.826
Name one cool guy
who doesn't talk.

09:25.913 --> 09:27.262
Snake Eyes
from G.I. Joe.

09:27.349 --> 09:28.437
Name one more.
Teller from Penn
and Teller.

09:28.524 --> 09:29.786
Name another.
Snoopy.

09:29.873 --> 09:31.788
He's the best.
Oddjob from James Bond,

09:31.875 --> 09:33.398
Jason Voorhees
and Michael Myers.

09:33.485 --> 09:35.357
All right, stop dancing
in the end zone!

09:35.444 --> 09:38.752
I couldn't wait any longer!
Have you chosen your suitor?

09:38.839 --> 09:40.971
ADULT ADAM:
While my matchmaking
blew up in my face,

09:41.058 --> 09:43.234
my mom was
about to drop a bomb.

09:43.321 --> 09:45.541
Bev, where are your dance
clothes and your leg warmers?

09:45.628 --> 09:46.803
Class is about to start.

09:46.890 --> 09:48.588
These legs
will never be warmed again.

09:48.675 --> 09:50.590
Why are you talking
so dramatically
about dance wear?

09:50.677 --> 09:52.592
I shared my gift of dance
with my family.

09:52.679 --> 09:54.681
And they laughed.

09:54.768 --> 09:58.032
So much so that Murray cracked
a bone in his middle body.

09:58.119 --> 09:59.381
Don't listen
to your family!

09:59.468 --> 10:00.817
Mine said we're
gonna be awesome!

10:00.904 --> 10:02.079
Same here.
Mine, too.

10:02.166 --> 10:04.429
That's 'cause they're kind,
stupid liars.

10:04.516 --> 10:06.823
I mean, no offense,
but anyone
who's seen Linda dance

10:06.910 --> 10:08.782
knows she's got no boogie
from the waist down.

10:08.869 --> 10:11.001
Excuse me?
Admit it,

10:11.088 --> 10:12.829
you jacked up your back

10:12.916 --> 10:14.831
carrying around your kid
for far too long.

10:14.918 --> 10:17.965
Geoff's 11-year-old legs
got tired easily.

10:18.052 --> 10:19.836
And don't get me started
on Essie's jazz hands.

10:19.923 --> 10:21.751
What's wrong
with my jazz hands?They are crooked

10:21.838 --> 10:25.755
