10:37.811 --> 10:39.160
Yes.
So intense.

10:39.247 --> 10:42.119
You know, truth is,
I'm still worse off than you.

10:42.206 --> 10:46.254
My family told me
I'll never be anything
but a lame-butt mom.

10:46.341 --> 10:48.386
No use fighting it.

10:48.473 --> 10:50.475
♪♪

10:50.562 --> 10:52.477
Not okay, Ginzy!
Go outside!

10:52.564 --> 10:53.870
The stress activates it.

10:53.957 --> 10:55.872
Stress activates it!

10:58.222 --> 11:00.094
ADULT ADAM:
I was losing Emmy
to the cool kids,

11:00.181 --> 11:01.922
so I turned to
the coolest dude I knew.

11:02.009 --> 11:04.228
Pops! Stop it
with the hamantaschen!

11:04.315 --> 11:05.621
I have an emergency!

11:05.708 --> 11:08.406
I was so close, but fine.
What do you got?

11:08.493 --> 11:11.192
Emmy has a super-popular
boyfriend!Good for her.

11:11.279 --> 11:13.237
No! She's gonna leave me
in the dust,

11:13.324 --> 11:16.023
which means I gotta
become super cool super fast.

11:16.110 --> 11:18.199
You want
cool lessons, huh?

11:18.286 --> 11:19.635
Well, you've come
to the right place.

11:19.722 --> 11:21.289
I don't have time
to learn stuff!

11:21.376 --> 11:23.944
I need an expensive shortcut
and I need it now!

11:24.031 --> 11:26.990
ADULT ADAM: It was red, it was leather, it was in the "Beat It" video.

11:27.077 --> 11:28.949
He who wore it
was a god amongst men.

11:29.036 --> 11:30.994
It's a fact.
Anyone who wears this jacket

11:31.081 --> 11:33.475
is automatically
the coolest badass
in the room.

11:33.562 --> 11:34.519
'Cause of
all the zippers?

11:34.606 --> 11:36.260
'Cause of MJ.

11:36.347 --> 11:39.524
And no kid on earth has one
'cause it costs $463.

11:39.611 --> 11:43.920
Whoa! You don't need this
farkaktespaceman jacket.

11:44.007 --> 11:45.705
Fine. I'm just gonna
call Emmy

11:45.792 --> 11:47.532
and tell her Shy Bri
is no good for her.

11:47.619 --> 11:51.449
No, that is
the least cool thing to do.

11:51.536 --> 11:54.452
Hello?
Hi, Mrs. Mirsky, it's Adam.
Is Emmy there?

11:54.539 --> 11:57.151
No. She said
she was studying
with you tonight.

11:57.238 --> 11:59.806
Emmy used me
as her nerd cover story.

11:59.893 --> 12:02.460
Oh, no! How sad for you
but smart of her.

12:02.547 --> 12:04.680
She's not there, is she?

12:04.767 --> 12:06.769
Of course!
I just forgot!

12:06.856 --> 12:09.685
She's making popcorn
in the popcorn room.

12:09.772 --> 12:11.643
Uh-huh.
Can I talk to her?

12:11.731 --> 12:13.167
Of course you can.

12:13.254 --> 12:15.778
Hey, Emmy!
Your mom's on the phone!

12:15.865 --> 12:17.649
Here she comes.

12:17.737 --> 12:20.000
She's walking to the phone
with the popcorn in her hand.

12:20.087 --> 12:22.654
Oh, no, she just
tripped and fell!

12:22.742 --> 12:25.092
Ohh, the popcorn
is everywhere!

12:25.179 --> 12:27.616
Oh! Oh!
Now, I just fell!
Gotta go!

12:27.703 --> 12:28.965
She has nev...

12:31.054 --> 12:33.404
I'm gonna buy you
the red jacket.

12:33.491 --> 12:35.711
ADULT ADAM: Once again,
Pops bailed me out.

12:35.798 --> 12:38.322
And thanks to the ridicule,
my mom bailed on dancing.

12:38.409 --> 12:41.108
Baby, I love you! You make
everything so much better!

12:41.195 --> 12:42.936
You shamed your mom
into quitting,

12:43.023 --> 12:44.764
who shamed my mom
into quitting, and then
everyone else quit

12:44.851 --> 12:45.808
and now the whole thing's
canceled.

12:45.895 --> 12:47.201
Well, you're welcome,
handsome.

12:47.288 --> 12:49.377
Wait. Bevy and all her friends
quit that thing?

12:49.464 --> 12:50.813
Thanks to your amazing
and cruel daughter.

12:50.900 --> 12:52.946
I was awful, too.

12:53.033 --> 12:54.512
BEVERLY: Dinner's served.

12:54.599 --> 12:56.819
If you need me,
I'll be upstairs in bed

12:56.906 --> 12:58.995
staring at the ceiling,
thinking about
what could've been.

12:59.082 --> 13:01.171
Cool.

13:01.258 --> 13:03.260
Um, what's the deal
with this sad lasagna?

13:03.347 --> 13:05.045
Mom's never made anything
in a casserole dish

13:05.132 --> 13:07.134
with less than eight layers.
What's going on?

13:07.221 --> 13:10.398
Clearly you morons
hurt the lady
and you're gonna apologize.

13:10.485 --> 13:12.269
Write one of your annoying
keyboard songs

13:12.356 --> 13:14.358
where you rap
and jump around.

13:14.445 --> 13:15.925
You know, the annoying crap
you do every week.

13:16.012 --> 13:18.319
Why just us?
You were laughing, too.

13:18.406 --> 13:21.409
Please, I'm her husband.
I never have to say I'm sorry.

13:21.496 --> 13:22.889
That's how marriage works.

13:22.976 --> 13:24.847
Okay, I'll get my Casio.

13:24.934 --> 13:26.544
And I'll get
my crazy mad flow.

13:28.372 --> 13:30.113
ADULT ADAM:
As they strolled off
to make amends,

13:30.200 --> 13:32.550
I was desperately hoping
my new red jacket
would make me cool.

13:32.637 --> 13:34.857
Hey! Beat it!

13:34.944 --> 13:37.251
Oh, yeah, sorry, right.
I'll get out of here.

13:37.338 --> 13:40.080
Nah, bro. Your jacket.
It's from "Beat It."

13:40.167 --> 13:42.822
This kid rules, 'cause look,
look, he's got the jacket!

13:42.909 --> 13:44.867
No biggie.
I've had it forever.

13:44.954 --> 13:47.391
Some say MJ
got the idea from me.Gnarly.

13:47.478 --> 13:50.525
Oh, so you're a bad,
gnarly boy now

13:50.612 --> 13:51.831
I have a girlfriend.

13:51.918 --> 13:53.920
That's part of it
for me.

13:54.007 --> 13:55.922
You making moves on my girl,
small fry?

13:56.009 --> 13:58.707
You're so dead, but sweet
jacket, so we're friends now.

13:58.794 --> 14:01.101
Okay, cool, man.
I'll catch you later.

14:01.188 --> 14:02.624
Adam?

14:02.711 --> 14:06.062
Dude, you suck, 'cause you
ditched me to hang here.

14:06.149 --> 14:07.324
Ain't that right,
that guy?

14:07.411 --> 14:08.848
Beat It!

14:08.935 --> 14:10.850
Are you kidding me?
I finally find someone I like

14:10.937 --> 14:12.286
and you can't even
be happy for me?

14:12.373 --> 14:14.331
Happy?
We're best friends!

14:14.418 --> 14:16.333
It's supposed to be
just you and me!

14:16.420 --> 14:18.945
We grow up together and live
next door to each other

14:19.032 --> 14:20.816
and raise our kids
side by side!

14:20.903 --> 14:23.819
No matter who we were with,
it was supposed to be us!

14:23.906 --> 14:26.126
You are such a hypocrite.

14:26.213 --> 14:28.693
Did I ever complain when I got
shoved into the background

14:28.780 --> 14:29.999
while you were
with Dana or Jackie?

14:30.086 --> 14:31.827
That's different
and you know it.

14:31.914 --> 14:34.047
How? I've been
the third wheel forever.

14:34.134 --> 14:36.179
Uh, this is
all super weird,

14:36.266 --> 14:37.789
and it's making me
feel like the third wheel.

14:37.877 --> 14:39.095
Why is he suddenly talking?

14:39.182 --> 14:41.402
See you in gym class
or whatever.

14:44.013 --> 14:46.668
Guess Shy Bri really opens up
on the weekends, huh?

14:46.755 --> 14:49.018
Don't talk to me.
Ever again.

14:50.802 --> 14:52.848
Beat it!
Yeah, yeah, the jacket.

14:52.935 --> 14:55.938
No. Actually beat it.
You're a bad friend.
Not cool.

14:56.025 --> 14:58.158
ADULT ADAM:
He was right.
I really did lose Emmy.

14:58.245 --> 14:59.986
Meanwhile, my mom
was about to get

15:00.073 --> 15:02.858
the most elaborate apology
in history.

15:02.945 --> 15:06.644
There she is!
Our flashy
little flashdancer!

15:06.731 --> 15:07.819
What is all this?

15:07.907 --> 15:09.691
You're about to witness

15:09.778 --> 15:11.562
the greatest apology ever.

15:11.649 --> 15:14.000
Behold!
A three-act hip-hopera

15:14.087 --> 15:15.958
so powerful
you'll forgive anything.

15:16.045 --> 15:17.699
JTP!
BOYS: JTP!

15:17.786 --> 15:20.528
Drop a respectful
apology beat!

15:20.615 --> 15:22.530
♪ Mom... ♪
Stop! It worked.

15:22.617 --> 15:25.315
I forgive you.
I can't stay mad at my babies.

15:25.402 --> 15:27.317
But, there's two hours left,
plus intermission.

15:27.404 --> 15:29.145
I'm fine.
Just go be kids.

15:29.232 --> 15:30.799
So we're good here?

15:30.886 --> 15:33.106
The kids are sorry,
you're back to dancing.

15:33.193 --> 15:34.890
Not yet.

15:34.977 --> 15:37.197
What about you?
Anything you want to say?

15:37.284 --> 15:39.590
Ha! You do
have to apologize!

15:39.677 --> 15:41.984
I do not! Do I?

15:42.071 --> 15:43.638
Okay. You don't get it,
do you?

15:43.725 --> 15:47.381
I expect my kids
to only think of me as a mom,

15:47.468 --> 15:49.339
but you're my husband.

15:49.426 --> 15:51.646
You're supposed
to think of me
as something more.

15:51.733 --> 15:55.084
♪♪

15:55.171 --> 15:56.607
Marriage is hard.

15:56.694 --> 15:57.739
Get out of my house!

16:01.221 --> 16:03.353
ADULT ADAM:
Even though my stubborn dad
hated apologizing,

16:03.440 --> 16:05.616
this time he'd
have to face the music.

16:05.703 --> 16:07.923
Oh, whatever this is,
I'm not in the mood.

16:08.010 --> 16:09.925
I'm just getting ready
for the big dance show

16:10.012 --> 16:11.274
at the Jenkintown JCC.

16:11.361 --> 16:14.538
Stop. Thanks to you, Murray,
I'm never dancing again.

16:14.625 --> 16:15.757
Oh, I get it.

16:15.844 --> 16:18.281
But there's gonna be
a Goldberg on stage tonight,

16:18.368 --> 16:19.761
no matter what.

16:19.848 --> 16:21.241
What are you doing?

16:21.328 --> 16:23.373
The kids gave you
an apology opera.

16:23.460 --> 16:25.680
I'm giving you
an "I'm-sorry" dance.

16:25.767 --> 16:27.203
Well, dancing
requires movement,

16:27.290 --> 16:29.162
which is what
you hate the most.

16:29.249 --> 16:32.165
I think you'll find me
shockingly agile.

16:32.252 --> 16:34.645
♪ Well, I hear the music♪

16:34.732 --> 16:36.343
Please stop.
Can't stop.

16:36.430 --> 16:37.866
Got flashdance fever.

16:37.953 --> 16:39.389
I just ate.

16:39.476 --> 16:40.477
Uh, okay,
here comes the good stuff.

16:40.564 --> 16:41.957
Ohh!

16:42.044 --> 16:44.046
That was a stupid,
stupid thing to do,

16:44.133 --> 16:46.266
moving your body
to music like that!

16:46.353 --> 16:50.313
You were supposed to stop me
and go to your dance recital.

16:50.400 --> 16:52.707
Well, everyone's right.
I am not a flashdancer.

16:52.794 --> 16:53.664
I'm just a mom.

16:53.751 --> 16:55.405
Not to me.

16:55.492 --> 16:58.104
You're beautiful,
you're brave, you're strong.

17:00.149 --> 17:02.412
Now I see why the kids write
their dumb songs.

17:02.499 --> 17:03.892
This stuff is really hard
to say.

17:03.979 --> 17:07.156
Now go get
your yenta friends and
get back on the dance floor.

17:07.243 --> 17:08.679
I made them all quit.

17:08.766 --> 17:10.333
Well, get them to un-quit.

17:10.420 --> 17:13.380
'Cause that's what my pushy,
amazing wife would do.

17:14.772 --> 17:17.210
♪♪

17:17.297 --> 17:19.212
ADULT ADAM: With that,
Beverly Goldberg
forced her friends

17:19.299 --> 17:21.040
back onto that stage.

17:21.127 --> 17:22.563
But within moments,

17:22.650 --> 17:25.392
my mom's harsh words came flooding back to all of them.

17:25.479 --> 17:28.699
And so, they completely forgot their routine.

17:28.786 --> 17:30.614
And then they rolled around
in a panic.

17:30.701 --> 17:32.529
Ginzy.

17:32.616 --> 17:37.882
♪ ...nothing but
a slow glowing dream♪

17:39.275 --> 17:40.537
Can we start again?

17:43.584 --> 17:46.021
Is she asking me?
Is this my decision?

17:47.805 --> 17:51.200
Look at me. We got this.

17:51.287 --> 17:54.160
ADULT ADAM:
And with one look,
my mom reminded them all

17:54.247 --> 17:56.510
why they signed up for that
class in the first place.

17:56.597 --> 17:59.034
They were moms, and that
meant they were tough.

17:59.121 --> 17:59.991
They were fearless.

18:00.079 --> 18:02.255
They were dancers.

18:02.342 --> 18:03.995
Kinda.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.824
Sure, their moves
weren't perfect,
but it didn't matter.

18:06.911 --> 18:10.350
That night, my mom
didn't win over a panel
of stuffy judges.

18:10.437 --> 18:12.265
She won over her
judgy family.

18:12.352 --> 18:14.397
Lookin' good, Beverly!

18:14.484 --> 18:16.791
I know her!
That's my mom!

18:16.878 --> 18:19.315
That's my wife!
She puts up with me!

18:19.402 --> 18:21.491
♪ ...for my life♪

18:21.578 --> 18:24.407
It was a moment my mom
and her friends
would never forget,

18:24.494 --> 18:26.279
and a night
I wish never happened.

18:26.366 --> 18:29.543
Oh, there he is.
How'd the jacket work out?

18:29.630 --> 18:31.284
♪♪

18:31.371 --> 18:33.590
Hey, kiddo.

18:33.677 --> 18:35.592
I thought Emmy and I would be
best friends forever.

18:35.679 --> 18:37.986
♪♪

18:38.073 --> 18:40.467
You know the greatest thing
about your best friend?

18:40.554 --> 18:41.990
What?

18:42.077 --> 18:46.037
Even if you drift apart,
you always find a way back

18:46.125 --> 18:48.953
and you pick up
right where you left off.

18:49.040 --> 18:51.260
You think?
You'll always be friends.

18:51.347 --> 18:54.133
Now go make this right
with her.

18:54.220 --> 18:57.223
ADULT ADAM: In that moment,
I realized some cool jacket

18:57.310 --> 18:59.050
wasn't gonna fix things
with Emmy.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.575
The answer
was to just believe
in our friendship.

19:01.662 --> 19:03.751
And so I rode
through the dark night

19:03.838 --> 19:06.014
to get back my best friend
in the world,

19:06.101 --> 19:07.581
even though
I knew in my heart

19:07.668 --> 19:09.452
it would change things
between us forever.

19:09.539 --> 19:11.367
Hey, open up!
We really gotta talk!

19:13.413 --> 19:16.416
Uh...why are you
at my window?

19:16.503 --> 19:18.853
'Cause I screwed up.
But you gotta let me fix this.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.464
I'd do anything
to make Emmy happy,

19:21.551 --> 19:24.641
even if it means she won't
be in my life as much.
So go get her back.

19:24.728 --> 19:27.340
I kinda never know
what to say.

19:27.427 --> 19:30.560
Lucky for you, her best friend
knows everything about her.

19:30.647 --> 19:32.997
♪♪

19:33.084 --> 19:35.086
♪ Pictures come alive♪

19:35.174 --> 19:37.611
♪ Now I'm dancing
through my life♪

19:37.698 --> 19:39.090
How'd you know
I got a thing for penguins?

19:39.178 --> 19:41.005
A friend told me.

19:41.092 --> 19:42.572
♪ What a feeling♪

19:42.659 --> 19:44.835
Wow. When you said
you'd set up Emmy,

19:44.922 --> 19:46.750
I didn't know you
meant Hot Brian.

19:46.837 --> 19:48.143
Easy.

19:48.230 --> 19:50.667
Well, she really is lucky to
have a best friend like you.

19:50.754 --> 19:53.279
ADULT ADAM:
Turns out Pops was right.

19:53.366 --> 19:55.542
Even if your best friend sets off on a different path,

19:55.629 --> 19:57.196
they never go too far.

19:57.283 --> 19:59.198
For me and Emmy,
we didn't end up

19:59.285 --> 20:01.461
living next door
to each other,
or even in the same city.

20:01.548 --> 20:04.203
But to this day,
whenever we see each other,

20:04.290 --> 20:06.944
we pick up
right where we left off.

20:07.031 --> 20:09.512
And it's not just
the friendships in life
that change.

20:09.599 --> 20:11.645
Sometimes,
those closest to you

20:11.732 --> 20:14.430
can surprise you in ways
you never imagined.

20:14.517 --> 20:16.650
All my mom wanted
was to prove to herself

20:16.737 --> 20:19.609
that she could be more
than just Beverly Goldberg.

20:19.696 --> 20:22.743
But in the end,
my dad made her realize

20:22.830 --> 20:25.659
that there really was
no one else in the world
that she needed to be.

20:25.746 --> 20:27.356
That's the thing
about family.

20:27.443 --> 20:28.792
There's no one better

20:28.879 --> 20:31.012
to put your heart and soul
on the line for

20:31.099 --> 20:33.449
than the people who loved you from the start.

20:40.761 --> 20:42.850
Okay, I'm here
with the real Emmy Mirsky,

20:42.937 --> 20:44.852
and I have a few questions
for you.

20:44.939 --> 20:46.680
So, how long
have you known Adam?

20:46.767 --> 20:48.334
Since we were six.

20:48.421 --> 20:50.901
ADAM: You only cried
a little.EMMY: Yes.

20:50.988 --> 20:53.774
Oops.
ADAM: You said...
Do we have that on tape?

20:53.861 --> 20:56.298
My favorite thing about Adam
is just that he's so funny

20:56.385 --> 20:58.648
and just being able to make
everyone around him laugh.

20:58.735 --> 21:00.911
You know, especially
when I go back and he shows me

21:00.998 --> 21:03.262
all these ridiculous videos
that he took.

21:03.349 --> 21:04.915
Like, we're just,
we're insane.

21:05.002 --> 21:06.917
We're complete lunatics.

21:07.004 --> 21:09.485
And for us, it wasn't really
like, oh, a boy and a girl,

21:09.572 --> 21:12.923
it was just like we were just
two crazy, bizarre kids

21:13.010 --> 21:15.099
just wanting to, like,
goof off all the time.

21:15.186 --> 21:17.972
The audience asks
every single time
there's an Emmy episode

21:18.059 --> 21:21.323
if, uh, if, uh,
you and, uh, Adam

21:21.410 --> 21:23.499
are secretly, madly, deeply
in love with each other?

21:23.586 --> 21:24.631
No.

21:24.718 --> 21:26.197
ADAM: Rawr!

21:26.285 --> 21:28.591
No. The answer is no.

21:28.678 --> 21:29.897
He's gonna be
very disappointed.

21:29.984 --> 21:31.115
I doubt that.
